spanishExample: El enfermero vio sus oídos y su nariz.
englishTranslation: The nurse(m) saw his ears and nose.

spanishExample: La boda es en ese lugar, entonces tienen que casarse.
englishTranslation: The wedding is at that place, so they have to get married.

spanishExample: La comida está buena hoy, pero tienes un poco en la frente.
englishTranslation: The food is good today, but you have a little on your forehead.

spanishExample: Estás alto y tu cabello está largo.
englishTranslation: You’re (getting) tall and your hair is (getting) long.

spanishExample: Espero que no se le ocurra nada o me va a dar un ataque al corazón.
englishTranslation: I hope he doesn’t come up with anything or I’ll have a heart attack.

spanishExample: El médico me dio medicina para la enfermedad.
englishTranslation: The medic gave me medicine for the disease.

spanishExample: Se te puede ocurrir algo para casarte.
englishTranslation: You can come up with something for getting married.

spanishExample: El médico me dijo que esta enfermedad va a ser mala para mi cabello.
englishTranslation: The medic told me this disease is going to be bad for my hair.

spanishExample: Me amaba y quiere que pueda casarme.
englishTranslation: She loved me and wants me to be able to get married.

spanishExample: Él está enfermo, pero ella igual lo ama.
englishTranslation: He is sick, but she still loves him.

spanishExample: La medicina es puesta por el enfermero en el brazo.
englishTranslation: The medicine is put by the nurse(m) in the arm.

spanishExample: Cuando duerme, puede ver su alma.
englishTranslation: When he sleeps, he can see his soul.

spanishExample: Tiene que hacer algo con su brazo y su pelo si se va a casar.
englishTranslation: He needs to do something with his arm and his hair if he’s going to get married.
vocabIncluded: casarse: any use of casar with a reflexive pronoun, changing the meaning to to get married

spanishExample: Es feliz y ahora se casa.
englishTranslation: He is(Ser) happy and now he is getting married.

spanishExample: Lo amaba, por eso quería que tuviera buena salud.
englishTranslation: I loved him; that’s why I wanted him to have good health.

spanishExample: Sus orejas pueden ser vistas desde lejos.
englishTranslation: His ears can be seen from far away.

spanishExample: Estoy enfermo, hay algo mal con mis oídos.
englishTranslation: I’m sick, there is something wrong with my ears.

spanishExample: Detrás de su frente está el cerebro.
englishTranslation: Behind his forehead is his brain.

spanishExample: Lo amas por su voz.
englishTranslation: You love him because of his voice.

spanishExample: No puede casarse hoy por la pierna.
englishTranslation: He can’t get married today because of his leg.

spanishExample: Tiene que amarte aunque tu salud no sea buena.
englishTranslation: She has to love you even if your health isn’t good.

spanishExample: Amo su voz y su alma.
englishTranslation: I love her voice and her soul.

spanishExample: Me caso y la boda es en mi casa.
englishTranslation: I’m getting married and the wedding is at my house.

spanishExample: Si te casas, no te diré lo que se me ocurrió.
englishTranslation: If you get married, I won’t tell you what I came up with.

spanishExample: La medicina fue puesta en el cerebro.
englishTranslation: The medicine was put in the brain.

spanishExample: No ha dormido porque no se ha casado.
englishTranslation: He hasn’t slept because he hasn’t gotten married.

spanishExample: Su pelo está detrás de la oreja.
englishTranslation: His hair is behind his ear.

spanishExample: Tuvo un ataque al corazón y eso fue triste.
englishTranslation: He had a heart attack and that was sad.

spanishExample: Han sido felices y la comida hoy estuvo buena.
englishTranslation: They have been happy and the food today was good.
